reviews.review_text: Chi-town 1/30/78 This is great 78'.The second set is a sizzle fest and the first set isn't to shabby either.Highlights for me were Ship of fools and the Eyes.
Jerry Saves great show, better than the Miller mix which is too low, Jerry explodes on his leads here, his voice is fine form and so is Bob, Donna sings low and in key and Keith adds nice flourishes,
